What did you say?

51
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:57,840
I said I was severely hurt.

52
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:59,280
This can make it heal faster.

53
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:01,600
You just talk too much.

54
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:02,640
Asking for a beating?

55
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:04,040
Better cover your mouth.

56
00:06:06,640 --> 00:06:08,000
Go back if there's nothing else.

57
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,120
I'm busy.

58
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,080
Don't disturb me.

59
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:13,360
There is something.

60
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:16,960
Sit.

61
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:20,600
Let me ask you.

62
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:23,000
Do you know which insect is the richest?

63
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:25,880
Answer me.

64
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:27,880
Crickets.

65
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:30,000
No. Silkworms.

66
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:31,160
Why?

67
00:06:31,440 --> 00:06:33,960
Because silkworms spin cocoons.
[*"Spin cocoon" sounds like "saving"]

68
00:06:37,280 --> 00:06:38,600
Sorry. I won't joke again.

69
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:40,800
I don't have time for jokes.

70
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,280
I need to work on medicinal food.

71
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:45,920
Medicinal food? You can ask me for help.

72
00:06:46,760 --> 00:06:47,760
What do I do?

73
00:06:47,840 --> 00:06:48,920
I'm an imperial physician.

74
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:51,000
Medicinal food's core

75
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,200
lies on the herbs, right?

76
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:53,960
It's my area of expertise.

77
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:55,800
I'm sure I'll be helpful.

78
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:58,520
